quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  3,78,"And indeed, of them is a group who twist their tongues with the Scripture, that you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>may think it from the Scripture while it is not from the Scripture. And they say, “It is from Allah,” while it is not from Allah. And they tell lies against Allah, though they know."
  3,79,"No person to whom Allah has given the Scripture and wise judgment and prophethood would ever say to mankind, “Be my servants apart from Allah.” Rather, “Be godly{1}on account of the Scripture which you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>used to <span class=",footnotes:1:Literally ‘Lordly’.,footnotes:2:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Ibn Amer, Asem, Hamza, Al Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…used to know and…”</span>
  3,80,"Nor would he command you to take the angels and the prophets as lords. Would he command you to denial after you became Muslims{1}?",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Muslimoonwhich means those who willingly submit to God, regardless of which prophet they followed.
  3,81,"And recall when Allah took the pledge of the<i class=""s"">(followers of the) </i>prophets, “<span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Nafie’ and Abu Ja’far read it as: “Inasmuch as We have given you…” Hamza read it as: “Because of what I have given you of scripture and wisdom, then a messenger has come to you...”</span>
  3,82,"So whoever turns away after that—those are the defiantly disobedient."
  3,83,"Do <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Abu Amr, Hafs and Ya’qub read it as: “Do you<sup><small>pl</small></sup> seek…”</span>,footnotes:2:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ya’qub read it as: “and to Him they return.” All except for Hafs and Ya’qub read it as: “and to Him you<sup><small>pl</small></sup> return.”</span>
